<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Capital Cities/ABC Inc.:
   Seven Magazines Are Sold
   To VS&amp;A's PJS Subsidiary
</HL>
<DATE>
06/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   CCB
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   ABC Consumer Magazines, a subsidiary of New York-based
Capital Cities/ABC Inc., said it sold McCall's Needlework &amp;
Crafts and six other special-interest magazines to PJS
Publications Inc., Peoria, Ill., a wholly owned unit of VS&amp;A
Communications Partners Limited Partnership, New York. Terms
weren't disclosed.
   McCall's Needlework &amp; Crafts, which features how-to
articles on knitting and other crafts, will become part of
the PJS Creative Women's Network, which also includes Crafts,
Sew News and a related magazine for the crafts trade,
Profitable Craft Merchandising. PJS Publications also
publishes Shooting Times and HQ (Handgun Quarterly).
</LP>
<TEXT>
   VS&amp;A Communications Partners is an investment affiliate of
Veronis, Suhler &amp; Associates Inc., a New York-based
investment banking firm.
</TEXT>
